CloudCore-AzureNetworkingOptions

Region - One or more datacenters within a specified geographic location

Virtual Network - Logically isolated network where resources cn safely talk to other resources in azure, internet and on premesis network. Scoped to a single region

Subnets - divide VNet into more parts, each part would carry a tier of an app

Resiliency - Ability of app to continue working during abnormal nature stuff or hacks

Azure Load Balancer - Balances the load by distributing incoming requests equally among all VMs

Azure Application Gateway - Load balancer designed for HTTP traffic, URL based routing to different VMs

Network Latency - Amount of time it takes for data to travel over the network

Azure Traffic Manager - Gets a request, uses DNS and then redirects it to geographically closest server cluster